  "description": "The MNE-Sample-Data dataset comprises simultaneous MEG and EEG recordings acquired from a single subject using a Neuromag Vectorview system at the Martinos Center for Biomedical Imaging. The experiment involved visual stimulation (checkerboard patterns presented to left and right visual fields, occasional central smiley faces) and auditory stimulation (tones to left and right ears), with concurrent structural MRI data acquired on a 1.5 T Siemens scanner. This dataset serves as a canonical reference resource for demonstrating MEG/EEG data processing and analysis workflows using the MNE software suite.",
  "methods_description": "MEG and EEG data were acquired simultaneously using a Neuromag Vectorview system with a 60-channel EEG electrode cap. Visual stimuli (checkerboard patterns and occasional smiley faces) were presented to the visual field with an inter-stimulus interval of 750 ms, interspersed with auditory tones. Subjects performed a reaction time task (key press with right index finger) in response to central face stimuli. Structural MRI was acquired using a Siemens 1.5 T Sonata scanner with an MPRAGE sequence. Freesurfer was used for anatomical segmentation and MNE tools for BEM surface generation.",
